 (Reuters) - President Barack Obama's economic team is 

 trying to craft a bank cleanup package that is flexible enough to solve the problem of bad debts and firm enough to quell taxpayer outrage over a Wall Street rescue. More details are likely to emerge in the next week or two, but the plan is expected to include a menu of options that could be applied to banks in various stages of distress. Here are steps that the Obama administration might take: